Test for zeroconf

data.text:
Marius:

This is not so easy to test autoip dhcp fallback.  autoip is straight forward -- it is setting a link local address. but in BOOTPROTO=dhcp4+autoip case, autoip starts when dhcp defers.

In the test suite, it make probably sense to block the dhcp server port for some time. Then autoip starts. after a while, dhcp lease arrives and removes the autoip address again. So it is a bit complex test flow to test this.

Currently, even though autoip is applied [as fallback], we continue to report setup-in-progress until dhcp arrives.
